title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1990-07-12
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Feel Like A Stranger, Bertha, A Little Light, Queen Jane Approximately, Stagger Lee, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Box Of Rain, Victim Or The Crime-> Foolish Heart-> Dark Star-> Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude Reprise-> Touch Of Gray, E: The Weight

Edie Brickell & New Bohemians Opened

reviews.review_text:
Great show--thanks for the matrix! I love this show, and despite the flaws in the Weight, they were clearly at the top of their game.

The soundboard sounds great with one exception--The Weight cuts out at the end, which is why I like this matrix copy best (the aud covers it). 

2nd set PreSpace is a must, from Take a Step Back and a hot Box to an excellent Victim, and a jammin' FOOLISH HEART->DARK STAR. The 1st set and PostSpace are real good, too.

Download this if you know how or contact me and trade, old school. I'm at barreramusic@gmail.com. My copy, though, is the board with an aud patch at the end of The Weight. Also, I took out lots of the track changes where you see this symbol: ->.  And I know it's sacrilege, but I edited out the DrumSpace segment entirely. Additionally, I carefully took out much of the interminable pausing between songs in the 1st set, cross fading the crowd from after a song to the crowd a bit before the next, as best as I could.
